is devoted to a hitherto little examined aspect of hand drawing and printmaking: How was hatching reflected upon in the period between c. 1500 and 1700? Central aspects of the artistic technique are examined on the basis of five case studies. The perspective extends beyond European national borders and seeks answers to this question. Methodologically, approaches of discourse history and reception aesthetics are combined. The promising source situation discloses a treasure trove of historical texts, many of which were transcribed and translated for the first time in this context. Detailed image analyses show the full potential of hatching and the way it functions in the artworks and their viewing. First monograph on the technique of hatching in the early modern period Previously unpublished image and text material  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDrawingxTechniquexHistory. 0aDrawingxTechnique. 0aDrawingy16th centuryxHistory. 0aDrawingy17th centuryxHistory. 4aClaude Mellan. 4aDruckgrafik. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aGrafik. 4aHendrick Goltzius. 4aKunsttheorie. 4aLuca Ciamberlano. 4aMichelangelo. 4aSchraffur. 4aVormoderne. 4aZeichentechnik. 4akünstlerische Technik. 4aÄsthetik.  aClaude Mellan.  aEarly Modern Age.  aGraphic art.  aHendrick Goltzius.  aLuca Ciamberlano.  aMichelangelo.  aaesthetics.  aart technique.  ahatching.  atheory of art.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978311076280840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076286040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110762860